        <p> There we first tried a parking space on the Elbe, which we had found on the Park4Night app. But when we arrived there, the space was unfortunately not there. Nothing to see the coordinates. So continue to the next parking space that should be on a rehab facility. But oh no - the square smelled so much of faeces that we are guaranteed not to settle here. So, still looking for a clean parking space, we asked politely whether we should at least empty our Pipitank. The answer? A clear "nope!" </p>
        <p> Then we only had the campsite in Pirna. After all, there was everything we needed for the night. The parking space was not the most spectacular, but at least functional. So we set up, threw the grill on and enjoyed the evening with cool drinks and the view of the bathing lake. </p>
        <p> And because life is simply not conceivable without ice, Basti quickly went to the ice cream stand after eating, get something nicely. Unfortunately, he brought the rain with him, soothes. Who would have thought that an ice cream could be so delicious in pouring rain? </p>
